        <title>Beware the Bat Cave</title>
        <author>
            <name>Rob Gale</name>
        </author>
        <link href="https://smpltn.com/beware-the-bat-cave.html"/>
        <id>https://smpltn.com/beware-the-bat-cave.html</id>
            <category term="styleframes"/>
            <category term="illustration"/>

        <updated>2021-03-23T16:13:29-07:00</updated>
            <summary>
                <![CDATA[
                        <img src="https://smpltn.com/media/posts/34/2021-03-23.jpg" alt="" />
                     With this piece I wanted to try getting myself more comfortable with Blender, so I challenged myself to start&hellip;
                ]]>
            </summary>
        <content type="html">
            <![CDATA[
                    <img src="https://smpltn.com/media/posts/34/2021-03-23.jpg" alt="" />
                
    <figure class="post__image post__image--center">
      <img loading="lazy" src="https://smpltn.com/media/posts/34/2021-03-23-2.jpg" sizes="(max-width: 48em) 100vw, 100vw" srcset="https://smpltn.com/media/posts/34/responsive/2021-03-23-2-xs.jpg 384w ,https://smpltn.com/media/posts/34/responsive/2021-03-23-2-sm.jpg 600w ,https://smpltn.com/media/posts/34/responsive/2021-03-23-2-md.jpg 768w ,https://smpltn.com/media/posts/34/responsive/2021-03-23-2-lg.jpg 1200w"  height="1080" width="1920" alt="" />
      
    </figure>

  <p>
    With this piece I wanted to try getting myself more comfortable with Blender, so I challenged myself to start the process of designing the environment in 3D. I'm a little slow with it because I'm just getting familiar with the way it works, but I can see how it could help speed the process along once I know what I'm doing. The trick is to keep it simple, knowing that I'm going to be going over everything with more detail in Photoshop.
  </p>

    <figure class="post__image post__image--center">
      <img loading="lazy" src="https://smpltn.com/media/posts/34/2021-03-23-2-2.jpg" sizes="(max-width: 48em) 100vw, 100vw" srcset="https://smpltn.com/media/posts/34/responsive/2021-03-23-2-2-xs.jpg 384w ,https://smpltn.com/media/posts/34/responsive/2021-03-23-2-2-sm.jpg 600w ,https://smpltn.com/media/posts/34/responsive/2021-03-23-2-2-md.jpg 768w ,https://smpltn.com/media/posts/34/responsive/2021-03-23-2-2-lg.jpg 1200w"  height="1080" width="1920" alt="" />
      <figcaption>3D render from Blender</figcaption>
    </figure>

  <p>
    Once I had the basic block in of the environment and the lighting set up, I went into photoshop to add all the textures and the characters to the environment. As I often do, I found most of the textures here from a variety of photographers on <a href="https://unsplash.com/">Unsplash</a>.
  </p>
            ]]>
        </content>
    </entry>
